My Growth Story:
Back in senior high, I started out as a quiet and shy student. My advisor even called me out directly about it, asking if I could really step up. That moment hit me hard, it was a challenge I couldn’t ignore.

I took that challenge seriously. By the 2nd and 3rd quarters, I ranked Top 1 in class, and overall I finished Top 3 with a 94 average. That wasn’t just about grades. It was proof that I could push past my comfort zone and grow when I put in the effort.

During our capstone project, I served as the assistant leader. I managed the initial product and handled the tech side alone. It wasn’t easy, but it taught me responsibility, initiative, and how to carry weight when the team needed it.

From being shy to proving myself academically and in leadership, I learned that growth comes when you accept challenges head‑on. That’s the mindset I want to bring into CPI — to keep building connections, strengthening communication, and stepping up whenever the org needs me.
